{"TopicId":27150,"ForumId":39,"TopicTitle":"The Pale Kerbin Dot","CreatedByName":"JRF2k","CreatedById":64440,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-16T18:58:21Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JRF2k","CreatedById":64440,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-16T18:58:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/cqOgGor\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/cqOgGor\u003C/a\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"astropapi1","CreatedById":57507,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-16T19:05:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWell, Kerbin is not literally a \u0022pixel\u0022 in that picture, but I still like it. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darkstrike","CreatedById":60004,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-16T19:52:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EJust as a note to any readers, and out of respect to such an amazing individual, the quotation is a modified version of the late, great, Carl Sagan\u0027s famous \u0022Pale Blue Dot\u0022:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/WmMUuR--Qvo?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JRF2k","CreatedById":64440,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-16T20:11:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022astropapi1\u0022 data-cite=\u0022astropapi1\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EWell, Kerbin is not literally a \u0022pixel\u0022 in that picture, but I still like it. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027ve not be farther than Minimus and Mun. I am sure someone else could make it better by getting out to Eeloo.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JRF2k","CreatedById":64440,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-16T20:12:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darkstrike\u0022 data-cite=\u0022darkstrike\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EJust as a note to any readers, and out of respect to such an amazing individual, the quotation is a modified version of the late, great, Carl Sagan\u0027s famous \u0022Pale Blue Dot\u0022:\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/WmMUuR--Qvo?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EShoot! I meant to mention that. Thanks for the assist!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"(An Original Name)","CreatedById":53457,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-16T23:22:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIts fairly simple too get really far out and see an even smaller Kerbin; just take any Minmus or Mun rocket, make a burn out of Kerbin\u0027s SOI at dawn or dusk, and just keep burning. A Mun rocket will probably have enough d/v to get you pretty far away from Kerbin, and all you have to do is constantly look at the planet while timewarping away. A telescope mod can help even more for this \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kahlzun","CreatedById":39989,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-18T15:31:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ehe looks way too happy for such deep thoughts..\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}